When building React Native apps, you often need to access device hardware or system services. This is where native modules come in. Native modules allow you to call Java or Swift code from your JavaScript code, but only when necessary. Use them to access camera, GPS, or file system. To create a native module, you'll use the `NativeModule` class. For example, to create a native module for camera access:

```javascript
// CameraAccessModule.js
import { NativeModules } from 'react-native';
const { CameraAccessModule } = NativeModules;
export default CameraAccessModule;

// CameraAccessModule.m
#import <Foundation/Foundation.h>
#import <React/RCTModuleMethod.h>

@interface CameraAccessModule : NSObject <RCTModuleMethod>
@property (nonatomic, copy) RCTResponseSenderBlock responseSender;

- (void)startCamera:(RCTResponseSenderBlock)responseSender {
  // Implement camera access logic here
  responseSender(@YES);
}
@end

```

Then, in your React Native code, you can import and use the native module:

```javascript
import React from 'react';
import { CameraAccessModule } from './CameraAccessModule';

const App = () => {
  const startCamera = () => {
    CameraAccessModule.startCamera((response) => {
      console.log(response);
    });
  };
  return (
    <View>
      <Button title='Start Camera' onPress={startCamera} />
    </View>
  );
};
```

Note that native modules can also be packaged as plugins, making them easily shareable across projects.

React Native's architecture has evolved over time. The new architecture, introduced in 2020, uses the JavaScript Interface (JSI) to improve performance and reduce the reliance on the React Native Bridge. JSI allows JavaScript code to access native APIs directly, eliminating the need for the Bridge. React Native Fabric, on the other hand, is a component that enables easy integration of native modules. Turbo Modules, a new feature in React Native, allow developers to create high-performance native modules using the Turbo Module API. Here's an example of using Turbo Modules:

```javascript
import { NativeModules } from 'react-native';
const { TurboModule } = NativeModules;
const turboModule = new TurboModule();
turboModule.init();
```

